<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3203] Rate-limit IO used by merging</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3203</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Large merges can mess up searches and increase NRT reopen time (see&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.mikemccandless.com/2011/06/lucenes-near-real-time-search-is-fast.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://blog.mikemccandless.com/2011/06/lucenes-near-real-time-search-is-fast.html&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple rate limiter improves the spikey NRT reopen times during big&lt;br/&gt;
merges, so I think we should somehow make this possible.  Likely this&lt;br/&gt;
would reduce impact on searches as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Typically apps that do indexing and searching on same box are in no&lt;br/&gt;
rush to see the merges complete so this is a good tradeoff.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
